pular volokh conspiracy blog a prolific and often controversial scholar professor bernstein is the author of several books lawless the obama administration’s unprecedented assault on the constitution and the rule of law encounter books  a conspiracy against obamacare the volokh conspiracy and the health care case palgrave macmillan  pb and hc coauthor rehabilitating lochner defending individual rights against progressive reform university of chicago press  pb  the new wigmore expert evidence aspen law and business  nd edition  coauthor you can’t say that the growing threat to civil liberties from antidiscrimination laws cato institute  pb  only one place of redress africanamericans labor regulations and the courts from reconstruction to the new deal duke university press  phantom risk scientific inference and the law mit press  pb  coeditor in addition to his books professor bernstein is the author of dozens of scholarly articles book chapters and think tank studies the law reviews that have published his work include the boston university law review california law review georgetown law journal  illinois law review iowa law review journal of supreme court history  law and contemporary problems  michigan law review  north carolina law review northwestern university law review notre dame law review  texas law review  vanderbilt law review washington university law review and the yale law journal  buy my books lawless the obama administrations unprecedented assault on the constitution and the rule of law you cant say that the growing threat to civil liberties from antidiscrimination laws more books product display system  bernstein david login sign up search expert search quick search patentsapps nonpatent literature search research mpep  tools  resources acclaim ip help title product display system united states patent application  kind code a abstract a product display system includes a hanger support member and one or more product hangers the hanger support member includes a web having opposite first and second sides the web has a corrugated profile defining a plurality of channels a plurality of receiving apertures extend through the web from the first side to the second side and define at least one row of receiving apertures extending across the channels a first product hanger may be mounted to the first side of the web through the row of receiving apertures and a second product hanger may be mounted to the second side of the web through the row of receiving apertures the hanger support member may be arranged for use with standard pegboard hooks inventors bernstein david roswell ga us application number  publication date  filing date  export citation click for automatic bibliography generation assignee bernstein david primary class  international classes af view patent images download pdf          pdf help related us applications selfabsorbent beverage holder coasterfebruary fratiannechelsea swing arm system assemblyfebruary spaldingtreemounted device for supporting animals and method of usemay mullisdisplay device for displaying memorial presentationapril colbertheight adjustable pad for use with inputs for electronic devicesjuly brophysupport for food product arrangement and method for assembling an arrangementseptember farid et alwrist rest apparatus having a solid structurenovember kuocord retention system for clothes pressing devicesaugust craiglowlocking device for computer equipment extension armjune derry et alhand positioner device for computer mousenovember kennedytote for conveyorseptember sorensen claims i claim  a hanger support member for supporting at least two product hangers to be mounted thereon the hanger support member comprising a web having opposite first and second sides and an axis extending from a first end to a second end a first channel and a second channel on the first side extending along the axis a third channel and a fourth channel on the second side extending along the axis and a first row of receiving apertures extending laterally across the first second third and fourth channels each aperture extending through the web from the first side to the second side  the hanger support member of claim  wherein the first row of receiving apertures comprises a first receiving aperture disposed in the first channel a second receiving aperture disposed in the second channel a third receiving aperture disposed in the third channel and a fourth receiving aperture disposed in the fourth channel  the hanger support member of claim  wherein the first and second channels are alternatingly interspersed with the third and fourth channels  the hanger support member of claim  wherein the web has a corrugated lateral profile defining the first through fourth channels  the hanger support member of claim  a second row of receiving apertures extending laterally across the first through fourth channels each aperture of the second row extending through the web from the first side to the second side wherein the second row is spaced axially from the first row  the hanger support member of claim  further comprising a flattened portion at the first end of the web the flattened portion extending laterally across a portion of each of the second channel and the third channel and an aperture extending through the flattened portion from the first side to the second side  the hanger support member of claim  further comprising a first flange disposed along a first lateral edge of the web and a second flange disposed along a second lateral edge of the web  the hanger support member of claim  wherein distal ends of each of the first and second flanges extend past a respective first or second side of the elongate body  the hanger support member of claim  wherein each receiving aperture has a circular shape  the hanger support member of claim  wherein each receiving aperture has a keyhole shape including a circular portion and a slot extending from the circular portion  a product display system comprising a hanger support member having a web defining opposite first and second sides and a corrugated lateral crosssection defining a first channel and a second channel on the first side and a third channel and a fourth channel on the second side each of the first second third and fourth channels extending along a longitudinal axis of the web extending from a first end of the web to a second end of the web a plurality of receiving apertures extending through the first and second sides of the web the receiving apertures forming at least one row of apertures extending laterally across the first through fourth channels the row including a receiving aperture disposed in each of the first second third and fourth channels a first product hanger and a second product hanger each product hanger comprising a bracket adapted to fit through at least one of the receiving apertures wherein the first and second product hangers are arranged to be simultaneously mounted to the opposite first and second sides of the hanger support member aligned with each other horizontally and vertically with the brackets extending through corresponding receiving apertures in a single row of apertures the channels being adapted to receive a distal end of the bracket from the product hanger mounted on the opposite side of the hanger support member  the product display system of claim  wherein the first and second channels are alternatingly interspersed with the third and fourth channels  the product display system of claim  wherein on each of the first and second product hangers the bracket is arranged to be received through a first receiving aperture in a row of apertures when mounted to the first side of the hanger support member and to be received through a different second receiving aperture in the row of apertures when mounted to the second side of the hanger support member  the product display system of claim  wherein each of the first and second product hangers comprises a body having an outboard side opposite an inboard side first and second brackets extending from the inboard side and a product support member disposed on the outboard side wherein the first and second brackets are arranged to be mounted in a first two of the receiving apertures in the row of apertures when mounted to the first side of the web and the first and second brackets are arranged to be mounted in a second two of the receiving apertures in the row of apertures when mounted to the second side of the web  the product display system of claim  further comprising a plurality of said rows of the apertures each row spaced axially from adjacent rows  the product display system of claim  further comprising a first flange disposed along a first lateral edge of the web and a second flange disposed along a second lateral edge of the web  the product display system of claim  wherein each product hanger fits between the first and second flanges when mounted on the first side with the first bracket of the product hanger disposed through the third receiving aperture and the second bracket of the product hanger disposed through the fourth receiving aperture  the product display system of claim  wherein each product hanger extends laterally across the web and rests against distal ends of the first and second flanges when mounted on the first side with the first bracket of the product hanger disposed through the third receiving aperture and the second bracket of the product hanger disposed through the fourth receiving aperture  the product display system of claim  wherein the distal ends of the first and second flanges extend beyond the first side of the web and maintain a gap between the inboard side of the body and the first side of the web  a product display system comprising a hanger support member having a web defining opposite first and second sides and a corrugated lateral crosssection defining a first channel and a second channel on the first side and a third channel and a fourth channel on the second side each of the first second third and fourth channels extending along a longitudinal axis of the web extending from a first end of the web to a second end of the web wherein the first and second channels are alternatingly interspersed with the third and fourth channels a plurality of receiving apertures extending through the first and second sides of the web the receiving apertures forming a row of apertures extending laterally across the first through fourth channels the row including a first receiving aperture disposed in the first channel a second receiving aperture disposed in the second channel a third receiving aperture disposed in the third channel and a fourth receiving aperture disposed in the fourth channel a first product hanger having a first body and first and second mounting brackets on an inboard side of the first body wherein the first product hanger is removably mountable on the first side of the web with the first mounting bracket disposed through the fourth receiving aperture and the second mounting bracket disposed through the third receiving aperture and a second product hanger having a second body and third and fourth mounting brackets on an inboard side of the second body wherein the second product hanger is removably mounted on the second side of the web with the third mounting bracket disposed through the second receiving aperture and the fourth mounting bracket disposed through the first receiving aperture description crossreference to related applicationsthis application is a continuationinpart of us patent application ser no  filed aug   which is incorporated by reference in its entirety hereinbackground field of the disclosurethe present disclosure relates generally to a product display system such as for displaying merchandise at a retail location description of the backgroundretail merchandise is displayed in many different ways at a retail outlet for example merchandise may be displayed on shelves or in racks the method of displaying the merchandise is often selected in a manner to enhance some consumer perception such as value desirability etcsome methods of displaying merchandise are intended to capitalize on the so called impulse purchase such methods generally include displaying a small number of relatively small sized product units in a location that is both immediately noticeable to the consumer and easily accessible sometimes these displays are placed in a location where a consumer is likely to have to wait for some period of time such as at checkout counters sometimes such displays are located along the general flow of traffic of consumers through a store and prominently displayed in a manner that literally stands apart from the surrounding products such product displays often include a hanging vertical display assembly including an elongate vertical body with multiple product hangers extending from one or both sides of a vertical base strip also frequently known as strip display assembliesstrip display assemblies come in many different forms one common strip display assembly includes an upstanding or hanging generally vertical support panel with a number of product hangers such as hooks or clips that extend from one side of the vertical panel products are hung from the product hangers and a consumer may easily remove one of the products from the strip display assembly by simply lifting it off the hook or removing it from the clip often these strip display assemblies are singlesided meaning that the hooks are disposed on only one side of the support panel such singlesided strip display assemblies however may not maximize the available amount of display space because products can only be displayed on one side of the support panelin order to overcome the limitations of the singlesided strip display assembly other strip display assemblies have been adapted to be twosided wherein product hangers are disposed on front and back sides of a generally vertical support panel such that products may be displayed on both the front and back sides of the strip display assembly rather than on only one side of the support panelstrip display assemblies often include removable product hangers that may be assembled to hang from the support panel in any of the many different locations to provide a more versatile product display system that is adaptable for displaying products of different sizes andor in different arrangements one common type of product display system includes a pair of vertically oriented support panels disposed adjacent each other with a space or gap formed therebetween each support panel includes a plurality of apertures therethrough and each display hanger includes one or more brackets or cleats that can be inserted into various ones of the apertures to releasably mount the product hanger to the support panel the two support panels are spaced apart so that the distal ends of the brackets of one product hanger do not interfere with the distal ends of the brackets of another product hanger when the two product hangers are mounted on opposite sides of the support panels aligned directly opposite with each other some general examples of systems generally similar to this are disclosed in shea us pat no  and in barkdoll us pat no  although versatile this style of strip display assembly often requires some assembly in the field in order to dispose the two support panels in spaced apart relationanother type of strip display assembly dispenses with the need to assemble the two support panels in spaced apart relation by providing only a single support panel that is vertically oriented for example by being hung from a hook display hangers are connected to the vertical panel with cleats that extend through apertures through the support panel display hangers can be hung on either or both of the front side and the back side of the support panel some general examples of systems generally similar to this are disclosed in shea us design pat no d and shae us pat no  however in this arrangement it is not possible to hang two display hangers on both the front and back sides of the vertical panel such that the product hangers are directly opposite or aligned with each other vertically and horizontally rather it is necessary in this type of strip display assembly for one product hanger on one side of the vertical panel to be displaced vertically andor horizontally from the other product hanger on the other side of the vertical panel so that the cleats of the one product hanger do not interfere with the other product hanger this effect can limit the versatility of this type of strip display assemblysummaryaccording to some aspects of the present disclosure a hanger support member is provided that can be used with known product hangers such as traditional pegboard hooks preferably the hanger support member can be used with the traditional pegboard hooks and with other product hangers according to the present disclosurein one exemplary arrangement of the present disclosure a hanger support member for a supporting one or more product hangers such as traditional pegboard hooks has a web defining first and second channels on a first side of the web and third and fourth channels on a second side of the web wherein the channels extend axially along the web at least one row of receiving apertures extends laterally across the first through fourth channels wherein each aperture in the row extends through the web the web preferably has a corrugated cross section extending between opposite lateral edges of the web and defining the first through fourth channels the first and second channels are preferably alternatingly interspersed with the third and fourth channelsin another aspect of the present disclosure a product display system includes the hanger support member and one or more product hangers adapted to be mounted to the hanger support member with one or more brackets that fit through the receiving apertures the product hangers and the hanger support member are arranged such that two product hangers may be mounted on opposite sides of the hanger support member in the same row of receiving apertures so as to be aligned with each other horizontally and vertically without requiring two vertical support panels with a space therebetween rather when a product hanger is mounted to either side of the hanger support member a space is formed by one or more of the channels between the hanger support member and the product hanger the space is sized or arranged to receive a distal end of the mounting brackets from the other product hanger mounted on the other side of the hanger support member directly opposite the one product hanger when the product hanger is mounted to one side of the web one or more brackets extend through corresponding receiving apertures in the row of apertures and into the channels on the opposite side of the web which are sized to receive the distal ends of the brackets from the product hanger mounted on the opposite side of the hanger support member preferably without extending beyond the surface of the opposite side of the webin further accordance with any one or more of the foregoing exemplary aspects andor arrangements a product display system andor any one more component thereof optionally may include any one or more of the following optional formsin some optional forms the first row of receiving apertures includes a first receiving aperture disposed in the first channel a second receiving aperture disposed in the second channel a third receiving aperture disposed in the third channel and a fourth receiving aperture disposed in the fourth channel preferably a second row of receiving apertures extends laterally across the first through fourth channels each aperture of the second row extending through the web from the first side to the second side the second row may be spaced axially from the first rowin some optional forms a flattened portion is disposed at the first end of the web the flattened portion may extend laterally across a portion of each of the second channel and the third channel an aperture may extend through the flattened portion from the first side to the second side for hanging the hanger support for example from hanger such as a hook nail or chainin some optional forms the hanger support member includes a first flange disposed along a first lateral edge of the web and preferably a second flange disposed along a second lateral edge of the web the flanges may be spaced apart laterally a distance sufficient to receive a product hanger therebetween on the first side with a first bracket of the product hanger disposed through the third receiving aperture and a second bracket of the product hanger disposed through the fourth receiving aperture the distal ends of each of the first and second flanges may extend past a respective first or second side of the webin some optional forms each receiving aperture has a circular shape or a keyhole shape including a circular portion and a slot extending from the circular portion the circular portion may be an elongated circular shape or an oval shapein some optional forms a bracket on a product hanger is arranged to be received through a first receiving aperture in a row of apertures when mounted to the first side of the hanger support member and to be received through a different second receiving aperture in the row of apertures when mounted to the second side of the hanger support memberin some optional forms the product hanger includes a body having an outboard side opposite an inboard side one or more brackets extending from the inboard side and optionally a product support member disposed on the outboard side the brackets are preferably arranged to be mounted in a first respective one or two of the receiving apertures in the row of apertures when mounted to the first side of the web and the brackets are arranged to be mounted in a second one or two of the receiving apertures in the row of apertures when mounted to the second side of the webin one arrangement a first product hanger and a second product hanger are removably mounted on opposite sides of the web at the same time in the same row of receiving apertures the first product hanger is mounted on the first side of the web with its first mounting bracket disposed through the fourth receiving aperture and its second mounting bracket disposed through the third receiving aperture the second product hanger is removably mounted on the second side of the web with its first mounting bracket disposed through the second receiving aperture and its second mounting bracket disposed through the first receiving apertureother aspects and forms will become apparent upon consideration of the following detailed descriptionbrief description of the drawingsfig  is an exploded isometric view of one exemplary arrangement of a product display assembly in accordance with the present disclosurefig a is a vertical horizontal crosssectional view of the product display assembly taken along the line aa of fig fig  is an exploded isometric view of another exemplary arrangement of a product display system according to the present disclosurefig a is a horizontal crosssectional view of the product display assembly taken along the line aa of fig fig  is a horizontal crosssectional view similar to fig a of another exemplary arrangement of a product display assembly according to the present disclosurefig  is an exploded isometric view of another exemplary arrangement of a product display assembly including a hanger support member and two pairs of product hangers in accordance with the present disclosurefig a is a partial horizontal crosssectional view of the product display assembly of fig  taken along the line aa showing one version of product hangers releasably mounted to the hanger support memberfig b is a partial horizontal crosssectional view of the product display assembly of fig  taken along the line bb showing another version of product hangers in the form of traditional pegboard hooks releasably mounted to the hanger support member andfig  is a front elevational view of the hanger support member of fig  the rear elevational view being substantially identical theretodetailed descriptionturning now to the drawings figs  and a show an exemplary product display system  including one or more hanger support members  such as a first and second or upper and lower hanger support members a and b and one or more product hangers  such as first and second product hangers a and b arranged to be removably mounted to either or both of the hanger support members a and b preferably the hanger support members a b are substantially identical and the product hangers a b are substantially identical and the letter designation “a” “b” etc identify different units of the same basic component each hanger support member  includes a web  that is generally vertically oriented having opposite first and second sides   a first spacer flange  a second spacer flange  and a plurality of receiving apertures  of which only four receiving apertures ad are specifically called out by individual references ad for clarity sake each product hanger  includes a body  having an outboard side  opposite an inboard side  a product support member  extending outwardly from the outboard side  and one or more brackets  such as first and second brackets a b extending outwardly from the inboard side  and arranged to be mounted in a diagonally offset pair of the receiving apertures  preferably the brackets  and the receiving apertures  are arranged such that the product hangers  may be releasably mounted to the hanger support member  to allow easy removal and rearrangement when desired the brackets a b and the receiving apertures ad are arranged such that the first product hanger a may be releasably mounted to the first side  of the web  with its brackets a b disposed through a first set a c of the receiving apertures  and the second product hanger b may be releasably mounted to the second side  of the web  aligned directly opposite the first product hanger a with its brackets a b disposed through a second set b d of the receiving apertures  so configured and as shown in fig a a distal end  of each bracket  is disposed in a space  between the web  and the body  of the opposite product hanger turning again to the hanger support member  the web  has a top end  a bottom end  and left lateral and right lateral edges   extending between the top end  and the bottom end  each spacer flange   forms a spacer on the first side  and a spacer on the second side  each spacer flange   projects in a first direction away from the first side  and projects in a second direction opposite the first direction extending away from the second side  the first spacer flange  is disposed along the left lateral edge  the second spacer flange  is disposed along the right lateral edge  each spacer flange   extends vertically along the respective lateral edges   each spacer flange   extends from the top end  to the bottom end  the spacer flanges   are parallel with each other and perpendicular to the web  the web  and the spacer flanges   form an isection extending from the top end  to the bottom end  thereby defining a recess or cavity that forms the space  on each of the first and second sides   of the web  said another way the web  and the spacer flanges   have an ibeam type construction with a crosssection that is shaped like the letter “i”each receiving aperture  extends completely through the web  from the first side  to the second side  preferably forming a tubular opening through the web  each receiving aperture  has an upper section  and a lower section  the upper section  has a first horizontal width and the lower section  has a second horizontal width that is less than the first horizontal width the upper section  is in the form of a horizontal slot the lower section  is in the form of a vertical slot extending downwardly from the upper section  together the upper section  and lower section  form a generally tshaped opening through the web the receiving apertures  are arranged in a plurality of quadrilateral arrays as shown by the dashed line  in fig  spaced apart vertically along the web  each quadrilateral array  is defined by four spaced part receiving apertures such as the receiving apertures ad arranged in a rectangular pattern such as a square having one receiving aperture  located at each corner of the rectangle a top pair of the receiving apertures such as the receiving apertures a and b defines a first horizontal row  such as upper row a and a lower pair of the receiving apertures such as the receiving apertures c and d defines a second horizontal row  such as lower row b although the depicted embodiment shows the quadrilateral array  as a rectangular array the quadrilateral array  may alternatively take other shapes including a trapezoidal shape for example with the receiving apertures a b being horizontally spaced apart wider than the receiving apertures c d preferably the quadrilateral array  is symmetrical about some vertical line such as the longitudinal axis of the hanger support member  the upper row a is vertically spaced from the lower row b a first distance or height and each quadrilateral array  is spaced vertically from an adjacent quadrilateral array  a second distance the second distance between adjacent quadrilateral arrays  may be the same as or different than the height of each quadrilateral array  in the exemplary arrangement the hanger support member  is shown with two quadrilateral arrays  thereby defining four vertically spaced apart horizontal rows  however additional rows  andor arrays  may be provided andor the length of the hanger support member  between the top end  and the bottom end  may be increasedturning again to the product hanger  the body  is in the form of a plate which is preferably flat on each of the outboard and inboard sides   the product support member  in this exemplary arrangement is in the form of a hook having a first end connected to the outboard side  and an upturned distal end spaced from the outboard side  however the product support member  may take other forms such as a cleat bracket or other support structures not shown arranged to support one or more pieces of merchandise the product support member  may include or be in the form of a clip in any arrangement the product support member  is arranged to support one or more units of merchandise such as packets bags clusters individual items or other units of merchandiseeach bracket  includes a shaft  and a head  the shaft  has a first end connected to the inboard side  of the body  and extends out from the inboard side  toward the distal end  the head  is wider than the shaft  in the horizontal direction that is the shaft  has a first horizontal width and the head  has a second horizontal width that is wider than the first horizontal width the shaft  and the head  form a flat horizontal plate wherein each of the shaft  and the head  has a horizontally aligned planer shape that is arranged to fit into the horizontal slot of the upper section  in each receiving aperture  the head  is sized to fit through the upper section  but not through the lower section  thus the horizontal width of the head  is approximately equal to or slightly less than the horizontal width of the upper section  and wider than the horizontal width of the lower section  the shaft  is sized also to fit into the lower section  the head  is disposed at the distal end  of the bracket  the head  is spaced apart from the inboard side  of the body  a distance equal to at least the sum of the width of the space  and the width of the web  in this arrangement the head  of each bracket  can first slide into and through the upper section  of a corresponding aperture  from one side of the web  then the shaft  can slide downwardly into the lower section  such that the head  engages the other side of the web  and prevents the product hanger  from disengaging from the web  while the shaft  is disposed through the lower section preferably an upper end of the lower section  has a constricted neck for example formed by a pair of opposing projections  disposed on opposite sides of the lower section  that is narrower than the remaining portions of the lower section  the projections  are spaced apart a width sufficient to form an interference fit with the shaft and to allow the shaft  to resiliently slide through the constricted neck thereby forming a snapfit locking arrangement for the shaft  to prevent the neck  from accidentally slipping out of the lower section  optionally the shaft  may have a tapered crosssection along the side edges rather than a rectangular crosssection to help guide the shaft into the constricted neck from the upper section  and to help the shaft  resiliently snap past the projections in the exemplary arrangement depicted in figs  and a the brackets a and b are spaced apart diagonally on the body  of each product hanger  the bracket a is vertically displaced or offset above the bracket b and each of the brackets a and b are horizontally spaced apart preferably symmetrically on opposite sides of a vertical center line of the inboard side  of the product hanger  the brackets a and b are arranged to engage opposite diagonal receiving apertures a c or b d in any one of the quadrilateral arrays  thus as illustrated in fig  relative to the product hanger a bracket a is arranged to fit into the upper left receiving aperture a and bracket b is arranged to fit into the lower right receiving aperture c in any one of the quadrilateral arrays  when mounted on or from the first side  of the web  similarly when the product hanger b is mounted on the second side  of the web  the brackets a and b fit into the opposite diagonal receiving apertures b and d respectively of any one of the quadrilateral arrays optionally some or all of the rows  on a web  are spaced apart the same height whereby the height of each quadrilateral array  is equal to the distance between each adjacent pair of quadrilateral arrays in this arrangement the brackets a b of any one product hanger  may also fit into diagonally adjacent receiving apertures in two adjacent quadrilateral arrays to releasably mount the product hanger  onto the hanger support member  the brackets a and b are inserted into respective opposite diagonal receiving apertures such as receiving apertures a c if mounted on the first side  of the web  or receiving apertures b d if mounted on the second side  of the web  the inboard side  of the body  engages distal ends of the spacer flanges   thereby forming the space  in the form of a gap between the inboard side  and the web  the space  is sized to receive the head  of each bracket  completely therein thus as best seen in fig a a first product hanger  can be mounted onto the first side  of the web  and a second product hanger  can be mounted onto the second side  of the web  directly opposite the first product hanger  both horizontally and vertically aligned therewith in this arrangement the head  of each bracket  mounted on one side of the web  is disposed in the space  on the other side of the web  formed between the web  and the body  of the opposite product hanger  on the other side of the web  thus in this arrangement two product hangers  can be attached directly opposite each other in vertical and horizontal alignment on opposite sides of the web  without requiring a second web with a space between two webs as in the prior artthe lower hanger support member b may be hung below the upper hanger support member a to extend the vertical length of the product display system  the top end  of the lower hanger support member b may be attached to the bottom end  of the upper hanger support member a by any sufficient mechanism such as a hook or clip  in one exemplary arrangement the lower hanger support member b can be hung from the upper hanger support member a by one or two product hangers a andor b for example the upper bracket a of the product hanger a can be inserted into a lower or bottom receiving aperture  at the bottom end  of the upper hanger support member a and the lower bracket b is inserted into a diagonally opposite upper or a top receiving aperture  at the top end  of the lower hanger support member b optionally the second product hanger b may be mounted onto the opposite sides of the webs  of the upper and lower hanger support members a b in a similar manner with the brackets a b mounted through the opposite diagonal receiving apertures  at the bottom end  and top end  of the upper and lower hanger support members a b respectivelyeach product hanger  optionally includes a pair of guide flanges   disposed along opposite lateral edges   respectively of the body  each guide flange   preferably extends from a top end of the body  to a bottom end of the body  along the respective lateral edge   however the guide flanges   may take other forms consistent with the functionality described herein the guide flanges   are spaced apart laterally sufficient to engage the spacer flanges   such as to be disposed along the outer surfaces of the spacer flanges   when the brackets a b are inserted into receiving apertures  as described previously herein preferably an inner surface of each guide flange   slidably engages an opposing outer surface of the respective spacer flange   in this manner the guide flanges   may help to guide the brackets a b into the appropriate receiving apertures  the guide flanges   may provide additional lateral stability for the product hangers  for example to prevent twisting of the product hangers  when hung on the hanger support member in some arrangements the guide flanges   may be offset inwardly between the spacer flanges   rather than being spaced outwardly from the spacer flanges   in such an arrangement the guide flanges   may also or alternatively serve as spacers to maintain the space  between the body  and the web  sufficient to receive the heads  of the brackets  as described previouslythe guide flanges   are sized andor arranged such that two product hangers  may be mounted directly opposite each other on opposite sides   of the web  and the distal ends of the guide flanges   on the opposing product hangers  will either fit tightly against each other or will be slightly spaced apart so as to not interfere or prevent the product hangers  from being secured to the web  as previously described each guide flange   is not longer than approximately half the length of the spacer flanges   andor the depth of the distal end of the spacer flanges   to the center of the web as shown in fig  a hanging assembly  is optionally disposed at or near the top end  of the web  the hanging assembly  includes one or both of a hanger receiver  such as an aperture extending through the web  and a hanger  such as a hook as exemplified in the drawings other forms of hanging assemblies  may be used that would be sufficient to hang the hanger support member  from some support member such as a rod or bracket a second aperture  may be disposed near the bottom end  of the web  and arranged to receive for example another hanger  such as a hook carried as part of a hanging assembly  in the lower support member b figs  and a show another example arrangement of the product display system  which is similar to the example product display system shown in figs  and a like the previous example the product display system  includes a hanger support member  and one or more product hangers  such as product hangers a and b that can be releasably mounted on opposite sides   of the web  the hanger support member  includes a vertically oriented web  extending between a top end  and a bottom end  a plurality of receiving apertures  extending through the web  and spacer flanges   disposed along opposite lateral left and right side edges   of the web  each product hanger  includes a body  in the form of a flat plate a product support member  in the form of a hook extending from an outboard side  of the body  and a pair of brackets a b extending from an inboard side  of the body  each product hanger  also includes a pair of guide flanges   disposed along opposite lateral edges   of the body  and extending in the same direction as the brackets  the product hanger  can be releasably mounted onto either or both of the first and second sides   of the web by inserting the brackets a b into corresponding ones of the receiving apertures  further two product hangers  can be releasably mounted simultaneously aligned directly opposite each other on opposite sides  and unlike the product display system in figs  and a however the receiving apertures  are arranged in a plurality of vertically spaced apart linear arrays such as horizontal rows  wherein each row  includes four horizontal spaced apart receiving apertures a b c d preferably the receiving apertures ad in each row  are spaced apart evenly and horizontally symmetric about a vertical centerline along the axis of the web  with first and second apertures a and b on the left side of the vertical center line and third and fourth apertures c and d disposed on the right side of the vertical center line as seen in fig  each row  of apertures ad may be vertically spaced from the adjacent rows  a distance equal to the horizontal distance between opposite ends of the row  or a different spacingalso different the brackets a b on each product hanger  are aligned horizontally and offset asymmetrically left or right between the guide flanges   from a vertical center line of the body  the brackets a and b are arranged on the product hanger  to fit into and through the receiving apertures b and d respectively if mounted onto the first side  of the web and to fit into and through receiving apertures c and a respectively if mounted onto the second side  of the w